<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id522fd2c3-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s117"><num value="117">§ 117.</num><heading> Oregon</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Oregon constitutes one judicial district.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I56" class="indent4 firstIndent-2">Court shall be held at Coquille, Eugene or Springfield, Klamath Falls, Medford, Pendleton, and Portland.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id522fd2c4-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/888">62 Stat. 888</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1950-08-03/ch514">Aug. 3, 1950, ch. 514</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/64/393">64 Stat. 393</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/91/272/s7">Pub. L. 91–272, § 7</ref>, <date date="1970-06-02">June 2, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/297">84 Stat. 297</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/106/518/tV/s502">Pub. L. 106–518, title V, § 502</ref>, <date date="2000-11-13">Nov. 13, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2422">114 Stat. 2422</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id522fd2c5-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id522fd2c6-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 183 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s102">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 102</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1122">36 Stat. 1122</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1945-11-06/ch447">Nov. 6, 1945, ch. 447</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/59/555">59 Stat. 555</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Provisions relating to appointment and residence of deputies by the clerk and marshal, and maintenance of offices by said officers, were omitted as covered by sections 541 [see 561], 542 [see 561], and 751 of this title.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes in arrangement and phraseology were made.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id522fd2c7-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id522fd2c8-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2000—<ref href="/us/pl/106/518">Pub. L. 106–518</ref> substituted “Eugene or Springfield” for “Eugene”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1970—<ref href="/us/pl/91/272">Pub. L. 91–272</ref> provided for holding court at Coquille.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1950—Act <date date="1950-08-03">Aug. 3, 1950</date>, provided for holding court at Eugene.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
